  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a complex legal issue with several key components in its framework:\n\n1. Key Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Act\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) guidelines\n\n2. Legal Definition\n- Process of concealing origins of illegally obtained money\n- Typically involves three stages: placement, layering, integration\n\n3. Regulatory Bodies\n- Financial Crimes Enforcement Network (FinCEN)\n- Department of Justice\n- Securities and Exchange Commission\n- Internal Revenue Service\n\n4. Compliance Requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Reports (SARs)\n- Customer Due Diligence (CDD)\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Transaction monitoring\n\n5. Penalties\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Significant financial penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- Potential imprisonment\n\n6. International Cooperation\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n- Cross-border information sharing\n- Coordinated enforcement efforts\n\n7. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Criminal investigations\n- Civil forfeiture\n- Regulatory sanctions\n\nThe framework aims to detect, prevent, and prosecute financial crimes.",
